ca.gedge.opgraph.app.components
Interface PathAddressableMenu

All Known Implementing Classes:
PathAddressableMenuImpl
public interface PathAddressableMenu

A menu that provides path-based addressing, to make menu-building a simpler task. A menu path is a sequence of alphanumeric strings separated by forward slashes (the '/' character). Examples:

  • file/open recent
  • edit/foo/bar/test
